# Citation File Format 1.2.0 — https://citation-file-format.github.io/
cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use MediaRef in academic work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "MediaRef: a portable frame-level media reference primitive"
abstract: >-
  MediaRef is a Pydantic-based primitive for referencing images and video
  frames by URI and nanosecond presentation timestamp. It provides lazy
  loading, optimized batch decoding for sparse video frames, and works
  across container formats (Parquet, mcap, rosbag, HDF5) without imposing
  any fps, episode, or directory-layout assumptions.
authors:
  - family-names: Choi
    given-names: Suhwan
    email: milkclouds00@gmail.com
repository-code: "https://github.com/open-world-agents/MediaRef"
url: "https://github.com/open-world-agents/MediaRef"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - video
  - dataset
  - machine-learning
  - pydantic
  - media-reference
  - video-frame
  - data-uri
  - mcap
